Class PathRestriction<A extends KeyableBean,B extends java.lang.Comparable<? super B>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.restriction.NonUnionRestriction<A>
      • gw.api.restriction.PathRestriction<A,B>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - Root type of the path. Must be an entity type.
    B - Leaf type of the path. Must be a comparable type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:

    public abstract class PathRestriction<A extends KeyableBean,B extends java.lang.Comparable<? super B>>
extends NonUnionRestriction<A>
implements com.google.common.base.Predicate<B>
    A restriction tied to a PersistentPath. The leaf property reference must have a feature type that is comparable.

      • makePredicate

        public com.google.common.base.Predicate<A> makePredicate()
        Builds a predicate that gets the leaf value from the specified input and then passes that value to the apply method.

        If the predicate encounters a null value or an incompatible subtype while traversing the path for any given input, it will return false rather than throwing an exception.

        Specified by:
        makePredicate in interface Restriction<A extends KeyableBean>
